  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UHG - ADM Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IFC, alongside ADM Capital (ADM) and a large European pension fund (collectively, the Consortium), is proposing to invest in Universal Saglik Yatirimlari Holding A.S. (UHG or the Company), one of Turkeys largest hospital networks and healthcare providers. 

The Consortium will provide capital to UHG to support its regional expansion across 1st and 2nd tier cities in Turkey.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will i) improve access to quality healthcare, particularly for publicly-insured patients; and ii) contribute to government movement to better integrate private businesses into health sector. UHG&apos;s national presence is anticipated to extend the reach of services and create stable employment to specialized medical personnel, even beyond the traditional Istanbul market.  The project may also be expected to strengthen over time the position of Turkey as a healthcare tourism destination.</narrative>
  </description>
